      <h2>Booking Tips</h2>
      <p>Observation class tickets for Kandy–Ella sell out weeks or months in advance during peak season (December–April and July–September) — book as early as possible through 12Go Asia or directly at Colombo Fort station. Second class reserved seats are easier to book but still worth securing in advance. Third class unreserved is always available and is the cheapest option — crowded but an authentic Sri Lankan experience for short sections. Take the morning train (departing Kandy around 8:30am) rather than the afternoon departure for the best light for photography.</p>
